3.palindrome:

t=int(input())
for z in range(t):
    n=input()
    if(n[::-1]==n):
        print("palindrome")
    else:
        print("not a palindrome")
-----------------------------------------------
4.reverse a two digit nummber such that it should not contain any zeroes in ones and tenths places
---------------------------------------------------------
n=int(input())
if(int(str(n)[:1])==0 or int(str(n)[1:])==0):
    print("sry")
else:
    print(str(n)[::-1])
